In the diagram below, $AB = AC = 115,$ $AD = 38,$ and $CF = 77.$  Compute $\frac{[CEF]}{[DBE]}.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.025 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F;

B = (0,0);
C = (80,0);
A = intersectionpoint(arc(B,115,0,180),arc(C,115,0,180));
D = interp(A,B,38/115);
F = interp(A,C,(115 + 77)/115);
E = extension(B,C,D,F);

draw(C--B--A--F--D);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, NE);
label("$D$", D, W);
label("$E$", E, SW);
label("$F$", F, SE);
[/asy]
